Parliament, Tuesday, 06 March 2018 – The Standing Committee on Appropriations will tomorrow be briefed by the departments of Basic Education and Transport, as well as community advocacy organisation Equal Education on learner transport challenges. Details of the meeting are as follows: Date: Wednesday, 07 March 2018
	Time: 09:00 am
	Venue: Committee Room M314, Third Floor, Marks Building ISSUED BY THE PARLIAMENTARY COMMUNICATION SERVICES ON BEHALF OF THE CHAIRPERSON OF THE STANDING COMMITTEE ON APPROPRIATIONS, MS YVONNE PHOSA For media enquiries or interviews with the Chairperson, please contact the committee’s Media Officer: Name: Ms Felicia Lombard
	Parliamentary Communication Services
	Tel: 021 403 8285
	Cell: 081 548 7011
	E-mail: flombard@parliament.gov.za Democracy is not an event that occurred in 1994. It is a process to which all of us can contribute by making our voices heard in Parliament, in the provincial legislatures and in broader society.Read more